{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":653,"text":"Hi. So today, I'd like to share\nsome works in progress."},{"time":3953,"text":"Since we are still realizing these works,"},{"time":6170,"text":"we are largely working within the realm"},{"time":7921,"text":"of intuition and mystery, still."},{"time":10026,"text":"So I'm going to try and describe"},{"time":11789,"text":"some of the experiences that we're looking for"},{"time":13916,"text":"through each of the works."}]},{"cues":[{"time":15639,"text":"So the first work is called the Imperial Monochromes."},{"time":18945,"text":"A viewer sort of unsuspectingly walks into the room,"},{"time":21940,"text":"and catches a glimpse of these panels"},{"time":24332,"text":"in a messy composition on the wall."},{"time":26507,"text":"Within seconds, as if the panels have noticed"},{"time":29059,"text":"the presence of the viewer,"},{"time":30684,"text":"they appear to panic and sort of get into"},{"time":33728,"text":"a strict symmetry."},{"time":35242,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":36985,"text":"So this is the sketch of the two states."},{"time":39133,"text":"One is total chaos. The other is absolute order."},{"time":41791,"text":"And we were interested in seeing how little change"},{"time":44142,"text":"it takes to move from one state to the other state."},{"time":47798,"text":"This also reminded us of two\nvery different pictorial traditions."},{"time":51528,"text":"One is the altar tablets of the 15th century,"},{"time":54081,"text":"and the other is about 100 years ago,"},{"time":56315,"text":"Malevich's abstract compositions."},{"time":59271,"text":"So I'm just going to take you to a video."},{"time":61287,"text":"To give you a sense of scale,"},{"time":62660,"text":"the largest panel is about two meters high."},{"time":64875,"text":"That's about this much. \nAnd the smallest one is an A4."},{"time":67693,"text":"So a viewer enters the space,"},{"time":69905,"text":"and they snap to attention."},{"time":72001,"text":"And after a while, if the viewer continues"},{"time":73989,"text":"to remain in the space,"},{"time":75717,"text":"the panels will sort of become immune"},{"time":77705,"text":"to the presence of the viewer"},{"time":79418,"text":"and become lax and autonomous again,"},{"time":82453,"text":"until they sort of sense a presence\nin the room or a movement,"},{"time":85828,"text":"when they will again snap to attention."},{"time":88527,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":90006,"text":"So here it appears as if it's the viewer"},{"time":92405,"text":"that's sort of instigating the sense\nof order among the panels,"},{"time":95650,"text":"but it could also be the other way around,"},{"time":97675,"text":"that the panels are so stuck within"},{"time":100019,"text":"their preconditioned behaviors"},{"time":102013,"text":"that they sort of thrust the\nviewer with the role of a tyrant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107541,"text":"So this brings me to a quieter, small work"},{"time":110039,"text":"called Handheld."},{"time":111608,"text":"The viewer sees a piece of paper"},{"time":113342,"text":"that's mounted on the far end of the wall,"},{"time":115812,"text":"but when you go closer, you see that it's a blank"},{"time":118440,"text":"A4, or a letter-sized piece of paper,"},{"time":120712,"text":"that's held on either side"},{"time":122029,"text":"by two small hands"},{"time":123970,"text":"that appear to be carved with a great deal"},{"time":126237,"text":"of attention and care from a small block of wood."},{"time":129710,"text":"The viewer also sees that this entire sculpture"},{"time":132706,"text":"is sort of moving very slightly,"},{"time":135168,"text":"as if these two hands are trying"},{"time":137029,"text":"to hold the paper very still"},{"time":138531,"text":"for a long period of time,"},{"time":140710,"text":"and somehow are not managing to."},{"time":143645,"text":"So this instability in the movement"},{"time":145618,"text":"very closely resembles the unsteady nature"},{"time":149136,"text":"of images seen through a handheld camera."},{"time":151698,"text":"So here I'm going to show you two tandem clips."},{"time":154386,"text":"One is through a still camera"},{"time":155806,"text":"and the other is through a handheld camera."},{"time":157884,"text":"And you immediately see how the unsteady nature"},{"time":160485,"text":"of the video suggests the presence"},{"time":163544,"text":"of an observer and a subjective point of view."},{"time":166031,"text":"So we've just removed the camera"},{"time":167860,"text":"and transferred that movement onto the panel."},{"time":170141,"text":"So here's a video."},{"time":171674,"text":"You have to imagine the other hand.\nIt's not there yet."},{"time":174113,"text":"But to us, we're sort of trying to evoke"},{"time":176860,"text":"a self-effacing gesture, as if there's a little person"},{"time":180399,"text":"with outstretched arms"},{"time":181990,"text":"behind this enormous piece of paper."},{"time":184492,"text":"That sort of likens it to the amount of strain"},{"time":187077,"text":"to be at the service of the observer and present"},{"time":189381,"text":"this piece of paper very delicately to the viewer"},{"time":192631,"text":"in front of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195394,"text":"The next work is Decoy."},{"time":197554,"text":"This is a cardboard model, so the object"},{"time":199342,"text":"is about as tall as I am."},{"time":201246,"text":"It has a rounded body, two arms,"},{"time":203135,"text":"and a very tall, head-like antenna,"},{"time":205346,"text":"and its sole purpose is to\nattract attention towards itself."},{"time":209243,"text":"So when a viewer passes by,"},{"time":211029,"text":"it sort of tilts from side to side,"},{"time":213844,"text":"and moves its arms more and more frantically"},{"time":216017,"text":"as the person gets closer."},{"time":219384,"text":"So here is the first test scenario."},{"time":221908,"text":"You see the two movements integrated,"},{"time":223797,"text":"and the object seems to be employing"},{"time":225786,"text":"its entire being in this expression of desperation."},{"time":230858,"text":"But the idea is that once it's\ngot the person's attention,"},{"time":233522,"text":"it's no longer interested, and it looks for the next person whose attention to get."},{"time":237594,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":240708,"text":"So this is the final fabricated body of the Decoy."},{"time":243740,"text":"It appears to be mass-manufactured"},{"time":245857,"text":"like it came out of a factory"},{"time":247559,"text":"like vacuum cleaners and washing machines."},{"time":249836,"text":"Because we are always working"},{"time":251339,"text":"from a very personal space,"},{"time":252747,"text":"we like how this consumer aesthetic"},{"time":255174,"text":"sort of depersonalizes the object"},{"time":257246,"text":"and gives us a bit of distance"},{"time":258977,"text":"in its appearance, at least."},{"time":260897,"text":"And so to us this is a kind of sinister being"},{"time":263237,"text":"which is trying to distract you from the things"},{"time":265356,"text":"that actually need your attention,"},{"time":266951,"text":"but it could also be a figure that needs a lot of help."},{"time":271725,"text":"The next work is an object,"},{"time":273897,"text":"that's also a kind of sound instrument."},{"time":276321,"text":"In the shape of an amphitheater"},{"time":278108,"text":"that's scaled to the size of an audience"},{"time":280048,"text":"as perceived from somebody from the stage."},{"time":282114,"text":"So from where I'm standing,"},{"time":283728,"text":"each of you appears to be this big,"},{"time":285390,"text":"and the audience sort of takes the entire"},{"time":287443,"text":"field of my vision."},{"time":289456,"text":"Seated in this audience are 996 small figures."},{"time":293418,"text":"They're mechanically enabled to clap"},{"time":295604,"text":"of their own free will."},{"time":297374,"text":"This means that each of them can decide"},{"time":299407,"text":"if and when they want to clap,"},{"time":300987,"text":"how hard, for how long,"},{"time":302619,"text":"how they want to be influenced by\nthose around them or influence others,"},{"time":306306,"text":"and if they want to contribute to innovation."},{"time":310286,"text":"So when the viewer steps in front of the audience,"},{"time":312803,"text":"there will be a response."},{"time":314487,"text":"It could be a few claps or a strong applause,"},{"time":317085,"text":"and then nothing happens until the viewer"},{"time":319269,"text":"leaves the stage, and again\nthe audience will respond."},{"time":322345,"text":"It could be anything from a few feeble claps"},{"time":324670,"text":"from members in the audience,"},{"time":326352,"text":"or it could be a very loud ovation."},{"time":330680,"text":"So to us, I think we're really looking"},{"time":332642,"text":"at an audience as its own object"},{"time":334939,"text":"or its own organism"},{"time":336655,"text":"that's also got a sort of musical-like quality to it,"},{"time":340405,"text":"an instrument."},{"time":341785,"text":"So the viewer can play it"},{"time":343541,"text":"by eliciting quite complex and varied,"},{"time":345977,"text":"nuanced musical or sound patterns,"},{"time":348673,"text":"but cannot really provoke the audience"},{"time":350949,"text":"into any particular kind of response."},{"time":353337,"text":"So there's a sense of judgment and capriciousness"},{"time":356081,"text":"and uneasiness involved."},{"time":358322,"text":"It also has an alluring and trap-like quality to it."},{"time":362431,"text":"So here if you see we're quite excited about"},{"time":364551,"text":"the image of the head splitting\nto form the two hands."},{"time":368373,"text":"So here's a small visual animation,"},{"time":370284,"text":"as if the two sides of the brain are sort of clashing"},{"time":374616,"text":"against each other to kind of make sense"},{"time":376643,"text":"of the duality and the tension."},{"time":379178,"text":"And here is a prototype."},{"time":381746,"text":"So we can't wait to be engulfed by 996 of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386548,"text":"Okay, this is the last work.\nIt's called the Framerunners."},{"time":389551,"text":"It comes out of the idea of a window."},{"time":392070,"text":"This is an actual window in our studio,"},{"time":394381,"text":"and as you can see, it's made up of three"},{"time":396299,"text":"different thicknesses of wooden sections."},{"time":398581,"text":"So we used the same window vocabulary"},{"time":400854,"text":"to construct our own frame or grid"},{"time":403681,"text":"that's suspended in the room and that can"},{"time":405623,"text":"be viewed from two sides."},{"time":407436,"text":"This grid is inhabited by a tribe of small figures."},{"time":410410,"text":"They're also made up of three different sizes,"},{"time":412975,"text":"as if to suggest a kind of perspective"},{"time":415401,"text":"or landscape on the single plain."},{"time":418112,"text":"Each of these figures can also run backward"},{"time":420557,"text":"and forward in the track"},{"time":422122,"text":"and hide behind two adjacent tracks."},{"time":425679,"text":"So in contrast to this very tight grid,"},{"time":427789,"text":"we wanted to give these figures a very comical"},{"time":430210,"text":"and slapstick-like quality,"},{"time":432299,"text":"as if a puppeteer has taken them"},{"time":434138,"text":"and physically animated them down the path."},{"time":436879,"text":"So we like the idea of these figures"},{"time":439159,"text":"sort of skipping along"},{"time":440695,"text":"like they're oblivious and carefree"},{"time":442783,"text":"and happy-go-lucky and content,"},{"time":445331,"text":"until they sort of sense a movement from the viewer"},{"time":448531,"text":"and they will hide behind the fastest wall."},{"time":452799,"text":"So to us, this work also presents\nits own contradiction."},{"time":456633,"text":"These figures are sort of entrapped"},{"time":458457,"text":"within this very strong grid,"},{"time":460604,"text":"which is like a prison, but also a fortress,"},{"time":463360,"text":"because it allows them to be oblivious"},{"time":465294,"text":"and naive and carefree and quite oblivious"},{"time":467999,"text":"of the external world."},{"time":470568,"text":"So all these real life qualities that I talk about"},{"time":473373,"text":"are sort of translated to a very specific"},{"time":475655,"text":"technical configuration,"},{"time":477416,"text":"and we were very lucky to collaborate"},{"time":479459,"text":"with ETH Zurich to develop the first prototype."},{"time":482627,"text":"So you see they extracted the motion cogs"},{"time":484892,"text":"from our animations and created a wiggle"},{"time":486982,"text":"that integrated the head-bobbing movement"},{"time":488936,"text":"and the back-and-forth movement."},{"time":490704,"text":"So it's really quite small."},{"time":492226,"text":"You can see it can fit into the palm of my hand."},{"time":494518,"text":"So imagine our excitement when we saw it"},{"time":496329,"text":"really working in the studio, and here it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":501622,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":505259,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506807,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}